This is a paved trail that has a couple of sections with stairs. There are multiple unpaved trail options to take along the route. 

Accessibility: Visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers may need to avoid the stair sections for safety. The most accessible portion of the trail is the Blueberry Hill Red Trail: https://www.alltrails.com/trail/us/new-jersey/blueberry-hill-red-trail. 

Accessible Parking:
Parking lot surface: paved;
There do not appear to be any public designated accessible parking spaces within 1.0 miles of the trailhead. There is a curb-cut to access the trailhead from the parking lot. 

Trail Details:
Trail surface: paved asphalt, a natural surface (dirt, grass);
Average trail width: 8 feet with a painted dividing line for some of the trail;
Estimated average grade category: mostly gentle (5% or less);
Known barriers: stairs at about 0,4 miles;
Benches: yes.

This is a natural surface trail with a very nice view of the NYC skyline. There are lots of trees and a variety of birds and geese. It is a good place to walk to get some fresh air and sunshine.

Accessibility: Visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers may need all-terrain tires or adaptive/motorized equipment for the surface type.

Accessible Parking:
Number of designated accessible spaces: 1 at the trailhead;
Number of van-accessible spaces with access aisles: 1;
Parking lot surface: paved.

Trail Details:
Trail surface: a natural surface (dirt);
Average trail width: 8 feet;
Estimated average grade category: flat (1% or less).

This is a quick loop trail with some scenic views of Atsion Lake. During the summer, the grass along the trail is usually overgrown so beware of ticks.

Accessibility: Visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers may need all-terrain tires or adaptive/motorized equipment for the surface type.

Accessible Parking:
Number of designated accessible spaces: 6 at the trailhead;
Number of van-accessible spaces with access aisles: 6;
Parking lot surface: paved.

Trail Details:
Trail surface: gravel, a natural surface (dirt);
Average trail width: 6 feet;
Estimated average grade category: gentle (3% or less).

This is the family-friendly Red Trail through Blueberry Hill Park. It avoids the hill and the stairs. There is plenty of nature to see along the way.

Accessibility: This trail is likely accessible for visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers. This is the most accessible portion of the Blueberry Hill Loop trail: https://www.alltrails.com/trail/us/new-jersey/blueberry-hill-loop.

Accessible Parking:
Parking lot surface: paved;
There do not appear to be any public designated accessible parking spaces within 1.0 miles of the trailhead. There is a curb-cut to access the trailhead from the parking lot. 

Trail Details:
Trail surface: paved asphalt, bumpy, cracks;
Average trail width: 8 feet with a painted dividing line for most of the trail;
Estimated average grade category: mostly gentle (5% or less);
Benches: yes.

This is a beautiful place for a relaxing walk with a spectacular plant collection. There is a mixture of paved and gravel paths. 

Accessibility: Visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers may need all-terrain tires or adaptive/motorized equipment for the gravel surface areas. Visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers may need assistance in the steeper sections or to avoid them for safety. According to the park website, the paths and gardens near the Haggerty Center and the Mansion are the most wheelchair-accessible areas of the park.

Accessible Parking:
Number of designated accessible spaces: unclear;
Parking lot surface: paved.

Trail Details:
Trail surface: paved asphalt, gravel;
Average trail width: 6 feet;
Estimated average grade category: mostly gentle (5% or less) with steeper sections at about 0.2-0.3 and 1.3-1.4 miles when going clockwise.

This is a gravel and wooden boardwalk path that loops around the forest. There are beautiful sights and benches along the way to sit down.

Accessibility: Visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers may need all-terrain tires or adaptive/motorized equipment for the surface type. 

Accessible Parking:
Number of designated accessible spaces: 2 at the trailhead;
Number of van-accessible spaces with access aisles: 2;
Parking lot surface: paved.

Trail Details:
Trail surface: gravel, wooden boardwalk with and without railings;
Average trail width: 6 feet;
Estimated average grade category: gentle (3% or less);
Benches: yes.

This trail starts on a paved loop around the pond and then takes a natural surface trail into the woods. This park also features sports fields (baseball, soccer), a lake, nice size dog runs (with separate runs for small and large dogs), enormous new playgrounds for the kids, wooded areas, pavilions for large groups/parties, and large open fields. 

Accessibility: Visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers may need all-terrain tires or adaptive/motorized equipment for the surface type between 0.2-0.9 miles when going counterclockwise.

Accessible Parking:
Number of designated accessible spaces: 2 at the trailhead;
Number of van-accessible spaces with access aisles: 2;
Parking lot surface: paved.

Trail Details:
Trail surface: paved asphalt, a natural surface (dirt, leaves, roots);
Average trail width: 6 feet;
Estimated average grade category: flat (1% or less).
